> Word on Trakanon 
> Posted: Monday, June 12, 2000 by Delsonora @ 3:36 PM EDT
> Add a comment on this article [0 Comments]
> 
> 
> Found this excerpt on the EQnecro site. It is a question to Abashi 
> about the toughness of Trakannon, the poison dragon who inhabits 
> Sebilis. Interesting.
> 
> Well we were exploring in sebilis last night, and were a few hours 
> in. We came to a big huge open room, then we see "Soando shivers and 
> shakes" then right in front of me I see Trakanon! The lvl 60 with us 
> conned him...red. Then he agroed. First aoe wave, 10dead...second aoe 
> wave, 10more. Then his guardians came, hitting for 300+. He himself 
> hit for dual 650's I heard from my groupmate. What I want to know, is 
> do you think he is fair and "doable" in his current state? Yeah I 
> agree he should be very hard, but an AoE dot that had to be at least 
> 300dmg a tick and an AoE DD that was 800 or more damage...along with 
> his guards bashing for 300...clerics arent gonna keep up with that.
> Anyway abashi, would you tell me if that sounds right to you? It 
> doesnt seem so...and if it is...I fear veeshan =)
> 
> Players have always surprised us with their ability to easily 
> overcome situations that we first thought were undoable, so I don't 
> think it will be too long before some, somewhere, show's Trakanon 
> whats what. It just takes a little while to refine the strategy.
> 
> -Gordon</TEXTAREA>
